### Critical / Blocking Findings
#### ❌ FAIL #1 — Broken Kotlin string interpolation in `pruneDanglingImages`
**File:** `koncerto-deploy/src/main/kotlin/com/flexsentlabs/koncerto/deploy/DockerLaunchCleaner.kt`
**Issue:** In `pruneDanglingImages`, the label filter argument is built with broken Kotlin string interpolation:
```kotlin
runDocker("image", "prune", "-f", "--filter",
    "label=$DockerEntityPolicy.MANAGED_LABEL=${DockerEntityPolicy.MANAGED_VALUE}")
```
`$DockerEntityPolicy` in a Kotlin string template interpolates `DockerEntityPolicy.toString()` — an object reference string like `com.flexsentlabs.koncerto.deploy.DockerEntityPolicy@3e57cd70` — and then appends the literal text `.MANAGED_LABEL`. The resulting argument is `label=com.flexsentlabs.koncerto.deploy.DockerEntityPolicy@HASHCODE.MANAGED_LABEL=koncerto`, which Docker cannot match.
**Effect in production:** The managed-label-scoped prune finds zero matches. `danglingAfterManaged > 0` is always true, so `docker image prune -f` (the unconstrained fallback) runs unconditionally, wiping **all** dangling images on the host — including those that belong to unrelated workloads sharing the Docker daemon.
**Fix:**
```kotlin
"label=${DockerEntityPolicy.MANAGED_LABEL}=${DockerEntityPolicy.MANAGED_VALUE}"
```
