#### ❌ FAIL #2 — Token-embedded remote URL logged verbatim
**File:** `koncerto-workspace/src/main/kotlin/com/flexsentlabs/koncerto/workspace/GitWorkflow.kt`
**Issue:** `setupOriginRemote` embeds the GH_TOKEN directly into the remote URL, then on every subsequent call logs that URL:
```kotlin
val existing = runGitSafe(workspacePath, "remote", "get-url", "origin")
if (existing != null) {
    logger.info("origin_remote_exists", mapOf("url" to existing))  // ← existing contains the token
    return
}
```
On the first call, origin is set to `https://x-access-token:<TOKEN>@github.com/...`. On every subsequent `createBranch` call for the same workspace, `git remote get-url origin` returns that token-embedded URL and it is written to the structured log verbatim. Any log aggregator, storage system, or observer of the log sink receives the live credential.
**Fix:** Redact the credential before logging:
```kotlin
logger.info("origin_remote_exists", mapOf("url" to existing.replace(Regex("x-access-token:[^@]+@"), "x-access-token:***@")))
```
Or use a credential helper instead of embedding the token in the URL.
