### Warnings
**W1 — Dead code in `DockerEntityPolicy.isProtectedContainer`**
The `isRunningStatus` branch unconditionally returns `true` at the end, making the four preceding `if … return true` checks unreachable. The function is correct (all running containers are protected), but the dead branches will mislead future maintainers into thinking the checks are load-bearing.
**W2 — Unconditional force push on any push failure in `GitWorkflow.commitAndPush`**
```kotlin
if (pushResult == null) {
    runGitSafe(workspacePath, "push", "--force", "-u", "origin", branch)
}
```
`runGitSafe` returns `null` for **any** non-zero exit — network timeouts, auth failures, lock contention — not just a history-divergence rejection. An auth failure will loop into a force-push attempt that will also fail, but a transient network error will force-push once the retry succeeds, silently overwriting remote history.
**W3 — Blocking I/O on the coroutine dispatcher in `DockerLaunchCleaner`**
`cleanOnLaunch` is `suspend`, but every private helper (`cleanOrphanContainers`, `cleanOrphanImages`, etc.) calls `ProcessBuilder.waitFor(30, TimeUnit.SECONDS)` directly. There is no `withContext(Dispatchers.IO)` wrapping. This pins a dispatcher thread for up to 30 s per Docker invocation and blocks whichever coroutine dispatcher calls this.
